'''Pine trees''' were a type of [[Tree/Legends|trees]]. They could be found on a number of [[Planet/Legends|planets]] like [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]], [[Krant]],<ref name="SW:GB">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Battlegrounds]]''</ref> [[Endor/Legends|Endor]],<ref name="HEST">''[[How the Ewoks Saved the Trees: An Old Ewok Legend]]''</ref> and many others.<ref name="SW:GB" /> Pines had needle-shaped leaves that emitted a sweet scent.<ref name="HEST" /> The painting ''[[Alderaan Refugees]]'',<ref name="Celestia">{{StoryCite|story=Celestia Galactica Photografica|book=Star Wars: Visionaries}}</ref> created after [[104 ABY]],<ref name="Date">"[[Celestia Galactica Photografica]]" was included in ''[[Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: Legacy Vol. 4]]'', which describes the stories it contains as taking place more than a [[Standard century/Legends|century]] after the events of {{Film|VI}}. The events of that film take place in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]] according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'', meaning that all [[Painting/Legends|paintings]] in "Celestia Galactica Photografica," including ''Hunting Overlook'', must have been created after [[104 ABY]].</ref> depicted pine trees on<ref name="Celestia" /> the [[Destruction of Alderaan/Legends|destroyed]] planet<ref name="IV">{{Film|IV}}</ref> [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]].<ref name="Celestia" />

==Behind the scenes==
In ''[[Star Wars: Galactic Battlegrounds]]'', pine trees are a source of [[Carbon/Legends|carbon]].<ref name="SW:GB" />

